    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Deserts characterized by a surface covering of rock and stones. Examples include desert plains having a surface veneer of gravel and stones or deserts on mesas or plateaus where constant weathering has stripped them of sand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
